to the editor ambassador richard c holbrooke suggests that the united nations transform its civilian run peacekeeping department into an effective military operation news article june 14 yet it is the reckless united states policy of arming combatants around the world without regard for regional stability or citizen security that has contributed to the depth and intensity of these conflicts the united states has sold weapons or provided military training to all five countries involved in the civil war in congo as well as to ethiopia and eritrea which have been locked in a brutal and unnecessary war with hundreds of thousands of casualties if washington slashed arms exports and placed more emphasis on diplomacy the number of crises demanding united nations peacekeepers would drop to a more manageable level j paul olweny washington june 14 2000 the writer is an associate africa demilitarization program center for international policy

